India Plans to Spend $10 Billion to Boost Its Forest Coverage by 2021

-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 
2011-05-09T11:11:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/india-plans-to-spend-10-billion-to-boost-its-forest-coverage-by-2021.html
India  plans to spend 460 billion
rupees ($10.3 billion) over 10 years to increase its forest
cover and improve the quality of existing woodland, the
government’s top advisory body said.  The proposed “National Mission for Green India” will
create 5 million hectares of new forest cover by restoring
mangroves and planting trees at abandoned mines, the Planning
Commission said in a report issued today.  The project also aims to improve the quality of 5 million
hectares of degraded forests, grasslands and wetlands, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  